d at ~80 ks in the observation. The\ntotal unabsorbed luminosity of 3C 120 implies that it is accreting close to its\nEddington rate, consistent with a model of an ionized thick disc. A connection\nbetween accretion disc thickness and radio jet production is discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 21 Jul 2004 15:33:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
